Early forms , with complex vertebrae consisting of a number of separate elements , were placed in the suborder Rachitomi , and large Triassic aquatic forms with simpler vertebrae were placed in the suborder Stereospondyli . With the recent growth of phylogenetics , this classification is no longer viable . The basic rhachitomous condition is found in many primitive tetrapods , and is not unique to one group of temnospondyls . Moreover, the dorsal margins of the vertebrae of mesosaurids are similar to those of Ichthyostega . The dorsal elements of Ichthyostega are distinct from those of Tiktaalik (see above), a marine teleost, and thus non-temnospondyl .
